│ This issue has been particularly challenging due to the interaction between two separate bugs in the InstCombine pass. My previous attempts failed because they did not correctly        │
│ address both issues simultaneously. I will now make one final, comprehensive attempt to fix both bugs.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ 1.  **The Regression Bug in `foldSelectToMinMax`**: The `select`-to-`maxnum` transformation incorrectly drops the `nnan` fast-math flag. This is because it intersects the `select`'s    │
│ flags with the `fcmp`'s flags. The `fcmp` instruction does not have a `nnan` flag, so the intersection clears it. The fix is to remove this incorrect intersection logic.                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ 2.  **The Original Bug in `foldSelectIntoAddConstant`**: The transformation `select(cmp, fadd(X,C), C) -> fadd(select(cmp,X,0), C)` is unsafe when the `fadd` has `ninf` or `nnan`       │
│ flags, as it makes a conditional operation unconditional. The fix is to disable this transformation when those flags are present on the `fadd`.                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will apply both fixes in a single, combined command. First, I will remove the faulty flag intersection from `foldSelectToMinMax`. Second, I will add the safety check to               │
│ `foldSelectIntoAddConstant`. This comprehensive approach should resolve both the original issue and the regression it exposed.                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i -e '/if (auto \*CmpI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(SI.getCondition()))/,+1d' -e "/if (!match(FAdd, m_FAdd(m_Specific(X), m_Specific(C))))/a \    if (FAdd->hasNoNaNs() ||               │
│ FAdd->hasNoInfs())\n      return nullptr;" llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
